o Malthus, from hunter-gatherers to the Romantics, from anarchist feminists to 1970s radical environmentalists, Limits shows us how an institutionalized culture of sharing can make possible the collective self-limitation we so urgently need.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEnvironmentalismxSocial aspects. 0aResource allocation. 0aScarcity. 0aSustainability. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aCastoriadis.  aLimits to growth.  aMalthusianism.  aRomantics.  aautonomy.  adegrowth.  aecological economics.  ahistory of economics.  ascarcity.  asustainable development.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070480808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020z9783110704600oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361156640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611566423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503611566.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070480-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPMb2020